President Biden met with Cabinet members and agency heads to discuss the 2023 Atlantic Hurricane Outlook and wildfire risk in the United States. They discussed efforts to prepare for extreme weather events and improve response and resilience. They also talked about new tools, such as advanced satellite technology, that are improving forecasting. The President highlighted his investments in community resilience and infrastructure, including funding for drought, flooding, and wildfires. He thanked first responders for their work in keeping communities safe.